@NODE "intro" "TIPic 0.23 - Introduction"
@PREV "main"
@NEXT "req"

 @{b}@{u}Introduction@{uu}@{ub}

 TIPic is a picture viewer for Texas Instruments (TI) 8x graphical calculators.
 Supported formats right now is : TI82, TI83, TI85 & TI86.


 Q : Why did I make this program ?

 A : I couldn't find any program on the Amiga that could show/convert
     pictures from my beloved TI83. (I had to use Macintosh-emulation to do so).
     So I decided to make an own program on the Amiga.. And here it is ;-)



 @{b}@{u}Features@{uu}@{ub}

 This programs features :

 · Show TI8x pictures (that is it's main point) ;-)

 · Export the pictures as ILBM pictures.
 · Fast and easy to use.
 · Drag & Drop support..


@ENDNODE

@NODE "req" "TIPic 0.23 - Requirements"
@PREV "intro"
@NEXT "usage"

 @{b}@{u}Requirements@{uu}@{ub}

 This program needs following stuff:

 · An Amiga (ohh gosh, you can't mean that) :-)
 · AmigaDOS 2.04 or higher..
 · Asl.library...


 That's it !.. And a little memory to :-)

 This program has been tested on following systems with success:

 Amiga 4000 (AmigaDOS 3.1, CyberStorm MkII, CV3D, 2 Mb Chip/64 Mb Fast),
 Amiga 3000 (AmigaDOS 3.1, Standard, 2 Mb Chip/ 4 Mb Fast),
 Amiga 1200 (AmigaDOS 3.0, BlizzardPPC/040, 2 Mb Chip/32 Mb Fast)


@ENDNODE

@NODE "usage" "TIPic 0.23 - Usage"
@PREV "req"
@NEXT "news"

 @{b}@{u}Usage@{uu}@{ub}


 @{u}Show a picture :@{uu}

 @{b}(I)@{ub}   - Use shortcut-key (@{b}Amiga-O@{ub}) to open the ASL-window
         choose the file you want to view....

 @{b}(II)@{ub}  - Or use mouse and pick "@{b}Open@{ub}" from the menu..

 @{b}(III)@{ub} - Or @{b}Drag & Drop@{ub} the file at TIPic's window..

 
 @{u}Save a picture (as ILBM picture) :@{uu}

 @{b}(I)@{ub}   - Use shortcut-key (@{b}Amiga-S@{ub}) to open the ASL-window
         choose name for the file you want to export as ILBM picture.

 @{b}(II)@{ub}  - Or use the mouse and pick "@{b}Save@{ub}" from the menu..


 @{u}Quit the program :@{uu}

 @{b}(I)@{ub}   - Use shortcut-key (@{b}Amiga-Q@{ub}) to quit the program..

 @{b}(II)@{ub}  - Or use the mouse and pick "@{b}Quit@{ub}" from the menu..





 @{u}Using TIPic from CLI/Shell :@{uu}
 
 In this version you can also start TIPic with an argument (if you want to)
 This argument should be the path+name of the file

 ex) TIPic ram:mario.83i

 If no argument is presented, TIPic will start as normal.
 And if the path and/or file name is wrong, the GUI will simply not show up and
 an error message will be shown. 
     
@ENDNODE

@NODE "news" "TIPic 0.23 - What's new?"
@PREV "usage"
@NEXT "history"

 @{b}@{u}What's new@{uu}@{ub}

 · Added CLI/Shell support (argument)
 · Fixed a stupid bug when drag & drop'ed a folder.
   (thanks J-C Perrier for reporting this)
 · Fixed so the latest filename used is showing in the ASL-requester.


@ENDNODE

@NODE "history" "TIPic 0.23 - History"
@PREV "news"
@NEXT "future"

 @{b}@{u}History@{uu}@{ub}

 · 08-06-1998 - First public ßeta-release (0.11ßeta)..

 · 19-11-1998 - (Release 0.22ßeta)

              · The whole program was rewritten.                
              · Added a better GUI.
              · Fixed a lot of bugs in the loader section..
              · Added ILBM-saver..
              · Drag & Drop support..
              · Added a guide documentation.
              · + numerous of other things ;-).

 · 01-12-1998 - (Release 0.23)

              · Fixed, so the latest filename used is
                shown in the ASL-window..

              · Added CLI-argument support, so it's
                possible to start TIPic from CLI using
                argument.

              · Fixed a bug when drag & drop folders..

              · Fixed yet another stupid bug ;-)

